recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2022-2023 F-150, Mustang, Explorer, Bronco, and 2023 Lincoln Aviator vehicles equipped with automatic transmissions.  The transmission may contain a loose bolt which could prevent the transmission from engaging the park gear, although the gear shifter position may indicate that the vehicle has been shifted to "PARK."
recalls.Consequence: The inability to secure the vehicle in the park position can result in a rollaway, increasing the risk of a crash or injury.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will inspect and, if necessary, replace the transmissions, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed April 25, 2023.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 23S06.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2023 F-150 vehicles.  The instrument panel top cover on the passenger-side may prevent the air bag from deploying as intended.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard number 208, "Occupant Crash Protection."
recalls.Consequence: An air bag that does not deploy as intended increases the risk of injury in a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace the passenger instrument panel top cover, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed March 16, 2023.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 23C01.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2023 F-150, Expedition, and Lincoln Navigator vehicles.  The front axle pinion may not have been heat-treated, which can cause it to fracture.
recalls.Consequence: A fractured pinion can result in a loss of 4-wheel drive and may cause the front wheels to lock up, increasng the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace the front axle pinion gear set.  If there is a broken front axle pinion, the entire axle assembly will be replaced.  Repairs will be performed free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed April 21, 2023.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 23S07.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2023 F-150 vehicles equipped with a single exhaust system.  Contact with the rear axle housing may damage the wiring harness, causing the electric parking brake to activate unexpectedly.
recalls.Consequence: Unexpected activation of the electric parking brake while driving increases the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will install a protective tie strap, tape wrap, and replace the harness as necessary, free of charge. Owner notification letters were mailed February 12, 2024.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 23S35.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2023 F-150 and Ford SD F250, F350, F450, F550, and F600 vehicles.  The steering wheel clock spring may have an insufficient weld, causing a loss of electrical connection to the driver's frontal air bag.
recalls.Consequence: A deactivated air bag will not deploy during a crash, increasing the risk of injury.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will inspect and replace the clock spring as necessary, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed on May 3, 2024.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2023 F-150 vehicles equipped with the Trailer Tow Max Duty package and a 9.75-inch heavy duty axle with a 3/4 float axle design.  The rear axle hub bolt may fatigue and break, which can result in damage to the axle hub splines.
recalls.Consequence: Damaged axle hub splines can result in a vehicle rollaway when the vehicle is in park without the parking brake applied or cause a loss of drive power.  Both of these conditions can increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace the left and right rear axle shaft assemblies, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed on May 9, 2025.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 23S65.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2020-2025 Explorer, Lincoln Aviator, 2020-2024 Escape, Lincoln Corsair, 2018-2024 F-150, Expedition and Lincoln Navigator vehicles.  The air bag warning label may be missing from the dashboard.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirement Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard number 208, "Occupant Crash Protection."
recalls.Consequence: Without a label that shows the proper restraint usage guidelines, the occupants may have an increased risk of injury in the event of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Ford will mail owners the warning labels, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed December 19, 2024.  Owners may call Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 24C39.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153) or go to nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2024 Bronco, F-150, 2021-2024 Edge, 2022-2025 Escape, F-250, F-350, F-450, F-550, F-600, 2022-2024 Expedition, 2022-2025 Transit, 2021-2023 Mach-E, 2024 Ranger, Mustang, 2021-2023 Lincoln Nautilus, 2022-2024 Navigator, and 2023-2024 Corsair vehicles. A software error may cause the rearview camera image to delay, freeze, or not display when the vehicle is in reverse.
recalls.Consequence: A frozen or missing rearview camera image can reduce the driver's view behind the vehicle, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: The accessory protocol interface module (APIM) software will be updated by a dealer or through an over-the-air update, free of charge. This will be a phased campaign, with the remedy becoming available in different phases based on model and model years. Interim letters notifying owners of the safety risk were mailed on June 26, 2025. Additional letters will be mailed once the final remedy is available on each phase. Owner notification letters were sent on October 8, 2025. Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332. Ford's number for this recall is 25S49.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 888-327-4236 (TTY 888-275-9171) or go to nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2023-2025 F-150 vehicles equipped with the Trailer Tow Max Duty package and a 9.75-inch heavy duty axle with a 3/4 float axle design. The rear axle hub bolt may fatigue and break, which can result in damage to the axle hub splines.
recalls.Consequence: Damaged axle hub splines can result in a vehicle rollaway when in park without the parking brake applied or cause a loss of drive power. Either of these conditions can increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace the left and right rear axle shaft assemblies, free of charge. This is a phased recall.  Ford owners will receive letters in multiple phases, beginning August 2025 through Winter 2025. Phase 1 will include 2023 F-150 model year vehicles. Phase 2 will include 2025 F-150 model year vehicles and Phase 3 will include 2024  F-150 model year vehicles. Interim owner notification letters informing owners of the safety risk were mailed August 22, 2025. Owner notification letters were mailed August 22, 2025. Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332. Ford's number for this recall is 25S82. This recall expands previous NHTSA recall number 23V896.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2022 Expedition, Lincoln Navigator, 2021-2023 F-150, 2022 F-250 SD, F-350 SD, and F-450 SD vehicles. The moonroof wind deflector clips may be inadequately attached to the moonroof frame, which can result in the wind deflector detaching from the vehicle.
recalls.Consequence: A detached wind deflector can become a road hazard and increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will inspect and repair the  moonroof wind deflector as necessary, free of charge. Owner notification letters were mailed November 10, 2025. Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332. Ford's number for this recall is 25SB7. Vehicle Identification Numbers (VINs) involved in this recall will be searchable on NHTSA.gov beginning October 30, 2025.

issues.title: Supercharger Belt Tensioner Failure
issues.description: The supercharger belt tensioner can fail prematurely, causing the belt to slip or come off completely, resulting in loss of power and potential engine damage
issues.fix_description: Replace supercharger belt tensioner and inspect belt for damage
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of belt system during maintenance intervals

issues.title: Fox Racing Shocks Leaking
issues.description: The high-performance Fox Racing shocks can develop leaks, causing reduced damping performance and oil stains
issues.fix_description: Replace leaking shock absorbers with updated units
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme off-road conditions and inspect shocks regularly

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing
issues.description: The SYNC 4A infotainment system can freeze or become unresponsive, affecting navigation, audio, and vehicle controls
issues.fix_description: Software update or module replacement if hardware failure
issues.prevention: Keep software updated and perform system resets when issues arise

issues.title: Transmission Shifting Issues
issues.description: The 10-speed automatic transmission may exhibit harsh shifting, delayed engagement, or shifting at inappropriate times
issues.fix_description: Transmission software update or valve body replacement in severe cases
issues.prevention: Regular transmission fluid changes and avoiding aggressive driving

issues.title: Brake Pedal Vibration
issues.description: Brake pedal vibration during normal braking, often caused by warped rotors from aggressive use or manufacturing defects
issues.fix_description: Replace or resurface brake rotors and inspect brake pads
issues.prevention: Allow brakes to cool after aggressive driving and avoid riding brakes

issues.title: Exhaust System Rattling
issues.description: The performance exhaust system can develop rattles due to loose heat shields or mounting brackets
issues.fix_description: Tighten or replace exhaust mounting brackets and heat shields
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of exhaust system components

issues.title: Air Conditioning Compressor Failure
issues.description: The A/C compressor can fail prematurely, resulting in no cold air and potential refrigerant leaks
issues.fix_description: Replace A/C compressor and evacuate/recharge system
issues.prevention: Regular A/C system maintenance and avoiding running A/C at maximum constantly

issues.title: Fuel Pump Issues
issues.description: The high-pressure fuel pump may fail or operate intermittently, causing engine stalling or poor performance
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel pump assembly and check fuel system pressure
issues.prevention: Use quality fuel and replace fuel filter as recommended

issues.title: Body Panel Alignment Issues
issues.description: Some vehicles may have misaligned body panels, particularly doors and hood, affecting appearance and fit
issues.fix_description: Adjust panel alignment or replace mounting hardware
issues.prevention: Inspect during delivery and address issues under warranty

issues.title: Tire Pressure Monitoring System Malfunctions
issues.description: TPMS sensors may fail or provide inaccurate readings, triggering warning lights
symptoms: system not recognizing tire pressure changes
issues.fix_description: Replace faulty TPMS sensors and reprogram system
issues.prevention: Avoid damage to sensors during tire changes and regular battery replacement

editorial.tagline: Desert-conquering supercharged fury meets everyday capability
editorial.hero_blurb: The Raptor R represents Ford's ultimate expression of desert-running capability, combining a 700-horsepower supercharged V8 with class-leading off-road technology. This is what happens when a Shelby GT500 engine meets the most capable off-road chassis in the truck world.
editorial.essence: The Raptor R is the apex predator of performance trucks, delivering supercar-level power through a chassis engineered to survive 100+ mph desert runs. It's the only production truck that can credibly claim to be equally at home on a drag strip or tackling the Baja Peninsula at triple-digit speeds.
editorial.heritage: Building on the standard Raptor's desert-racing DNA first established in 2010, the Raptor R debuted in 2023 as Ford's answer to Ram's TRX. It borrows the heart of the Shelby GT500 Mustang and wraps it in the most sophisticated off-road truck platform ever created.
editorial.design_philosophy: Maximum capability without compromise - designers sought to create a truck that could dominate both on-road performance and extreme off-road conditions while maintaining daily drivability and Ford's signature truck utility.
editorial.motorsport_history: Descended from Ford's Baja 1000-winning F-150 race trucks and the high-performance Raptor line that has dominated desert racing since its introduction. The supercharged engine traces its lineage to Ford's GT500 road racing heritage.
editorial.engine_character: The supercharged 5.2L Predator V8 delivers instant, explosive power with a linear surge that builds relentlessly to redline. There's no lag, no waiting - just immediate, violent acceleration that pins you to the seat while the supercharger whine builds to a crescendo.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 10-speed automatic shifts with decisive precision in Normal mode but becomes more aggressive in Sport, holding gears longer and delivering rapid-fire downshifts. In off-road modes, it intelligently manages torque delivery for maximum traction.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The Fox Live Valve dampers constantly adapt to terrain, providing incredible composure at speed over rough surfaces while maintaining planted on-road behavior. The chassis feels bulletproof yet surprisingly refined for such an extreme machine.
editorial.steering_feel: Precise and confidence-inspiring on-road with excellent highway stability, while providing the lock-to-lock travel needed for technical off-road work. The variable-ratio system seamlessly adapts from parking lot maneuvers to high-speed desert running.
editorial.brake_confidence: Massive Brembo brakes provide fade-resistant stopping power that matches the truck's performance capabilities. Pedal feel is firm and progressive, inspiring confidence whether hauling down from triple digits or navigating technical terrain.
editorial.sound_signature: A symphony of American muscle - the supercharger's rising whine layered over the deep-throated V8 rumble, punctuated by aggressive exhaust pops on overrun. The sound alone is worth the price of admission.
editorial.ideal_owner: Performance truck enthusiasts who want the ultimate expression of American muscle in truck form, serious off-road adventurers who need maximum capability, and collectors seeking the apex of the current truck performance wars.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Budget-conscious buyers, those prioritizing fuel economy, urban dwellers with tight parking situations, or anyone who doesn't appreciate the truck's aggressive character and substantial presence.
editorial.buyers_summary: The Raptor R is as close to a perfect performance truck as currently exists, though it commands a significant premium over the standard Raptor. If maximum capability and exclusivity matter more than value, nothing else comes close to matching its combination of power and off-road prowess.
